# FastAPI Auth Template

Reusable FastAPI backend template with:
- user signup + email verification activation
- login/logout with JWT access+refresh tokens and Redis session invalidation
- forgot password + reset password
- OTP email login
- token verification endpoint
- users, groups, permissions (RBAC)
- AWS S3 profile/file upload metadata
- Alembic migrations
- Docker Compose stack with PostgreSQL, Redis, and Mailpit

## Stack
- FastAPI
- PostgreSQL
- Alembic
- Redis
- Docker + Docker Compose
- Mailpit (local email testing)
- AWS S3 (with optional MinIO profile in compose)

## Local Setup (Mac)
1. Copy env:
   - `cp .env.example .env`
2. Install dependencies:
   - `pip3 install -e .`
3. Run migrations:
   - `alembic upgrade head`
4. Start API:
   - `uvicorn app.main:app --reload`

## Docker Setup
1. Copy env:
   - `cp .env.example .env`
2. Start stack:
   - `docker compose up --build`
3. Open:
   - API docs: `http://localhost:8000/docs`
   - Mailpit UI: `http://localhost:8025`

## Alembic Commands
- Create revision:
  - `alembic revision -m "your_message"`
- Autogenerate revision:
  - `alembic revision --autogenerate -m "your_message"`
- Upgrade DB:
  - `alembic upgrade head`
- Downgrade one revision:
  - `alembic downgrade -1`

## Test
- `pip3 install -e .[dev]`
- `pytest -q`

## API Endpoints
- `POST /api/v1/auth/signup`
- `POST /api/v1/auth/verify-email`
- `POST /api/v1/auth/login`
- `POST /api/v1/auth/logout`
- `POST /api/v1/auth/forgot-password`
- `POST /api/v1/auth/reset-password`
- `POST /api/v1/auth/request-otp`
- `POST /api/v1/auth/login-otp`
- `GET /api/v1/auth/verify-token`
- `GET /api/v1/users/me`
- `GET /api/v1/users/me/permissions`
- `POST /api/v1/users/me/profile-picture`
